Peel and very finely chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped) and the @garlic clove{1}(finely chopped). Chop the @cauliflower{1/2}(cut into bite-sized florets). Roughly chop the @coriander{1/2}(roughly chopped). Chop the @green beans{1}(cut into thirds, ends discarded).

> If the onion starts to brown turn the heat down a bit.

Heat a splash of oil in a large #pot{} on medium-low heat. Add your onion and garlic and slowly cook for ~{5%minutes}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a few grinds of @pepper{a few grinds}.

Once your onions are soft, add the @curry powder mix{1%tsp} and stir.

Stir in the @tomato puree{1%tsp} and then add the @organic chopped tomatoes{1%400g can}. Add another pinch of @salt{pinch} and a sprinkle of @?sugar{sprinkle} (if you have some). Add the @red split lentils{100%g}, the @water{200%ml} and the @vegetable stock pot{1}. Bring to a gentle simmer, put a lid on and leave for ~{5%minutes}.

Remove the lid and add your cauliflower. Cook for around ~{10%minutes} or until your cauliflower is tender.

When your cauliflower is halfway through cooking add your green beans and cook for ~{5%minutes} more.

> Don't worry if the dal is drying out a little – just add a bit more water to get a looser consistency.

Stir through your coriander and some of the @greek style yoghurt{1/2%small pot}.

> At this stage it's crucial to taste for seasoning - have a spoonful and add more salt and pepper to lift the flavours to their max!

Serve with a little more coriander and a nice big dollop of yoghurt.